So, my computer has been busted for a couple weeks and now it is finally fixed again.  I miss my husband, where the hell have you've been?
  I have been in such a great mood this past week, it has been awesome, yet, really wierd at the same time.  Been working my ass off and now getting ready to pack up my whole apt and do another move...what a pain in the butt.  
  I have a date next Friday that I am also really nervous about.  More like butterflies in my stomache, so many that I want to throw up everytime I think about it.  Haven't been on a real date in ages...and if someone told me that I'd be going on a date with my Rockstar to His show, I would have not believed them...we'll see how it goes.
  Tonite going to be in the city watching Cole play at Bar 169...come out if anyone wants to:)

So much craziness has been going on in my life this past week.  Karma is a BITCH, let me tell you.  This is payback for what I did to him.  I knew one day it would come back and bite me in the butt, I guess better now then later.  One good thing thou, out of all this craziness, I still managed to have met my ROCK Star...good friend to have if not anything more.

We're back together...my goodness I can't believe there are still such great people left in this miserable world
He loves me *sigh*  Love IS complicated...back to square zero, but at least we're here together.

"Without you , there'd be no sun in my life.  There would be no love in my life, no world left for me"  how true are those word in that song.  How do I live *sigh*  This part of the morning is alwayz the hardest without you...why did you have to spoil me so now I can't sleep a wink without being curled up in your arms.  Time will heal all wounds, so it has been proven...but, hat time it takes is going to be a bitch to get through.  Love *sigh* it's so fucking complicated.

*sigh* fucking up sure sux...but at least this thing has blown over...with the exception of just one of my friends not talking to me verse 4 out of the 10 of my friends.  I have never gone through so many emtions as I have in the past week.  I don't know what the hell is wrong with me?  Wow, what a way to find out that  GUY LOVES YOU...WHEN YOU FUCK UP*SIGH*

Happy 420 to start this entry off, it has one month and one week since my last livejournal entry.  Sorry about that but I have just been busy and havn't really had the time to update.  Finally it is getting warmer and finally no more SNOW!  Spring officially arrived March 20th, just happens to be the day after I got involved with you:)  My Harry Potter you were so much better in my dreams and when I could just imagine the things we would do together...who would have ever thought that you would end up being such a jerk.  
  However, a guility concience does get me good hook-ups at Blue Ribbon...lol.  But that was so over pretty much a month ago...or it never even began.  Now YOU, though, you were def. not a mistake and def. something I cherish.  It has been a month exactly since we first started this non-relationship and let me tell you I have never been happier with a non-relationship.  Usually by this time I am running away or wondering where this is going, but this time it is just different.  I think because I know that whatever happens with "us" we'll alwayz be friends...and that is all the security that I need.
  Califoniria is looking more promising each cold day that goes by...now I have someone who wants to move too....DON'T DISApPEAR ON ME BEFORE THEN...you know who you are miss sudden
 depature...
  This endless nite has been good, nothing like spending it with a few close friends and part of it with some good friends...it is good change from spending it with, you know...not that I don't enjoy every sec. we spend together but I need to show my friends love too:)  
  Okay enough for this entry, I'll try to keep on top of this journal thing and keep updating...
  Hey, friend, that keeps ditching me, you know who you are...I know you still read my journal at least so at least you know that am still alive and well:)
  Apparently that has become the question of the year "Where the hell did this girl go?"

SNOW...not the kind you snort either...all over the city floor.  It was snowing yesterday and now the snow has stuck onto the the dirty ground.  At least it is my last day of work for my after-school job, for the next two weeks at least...woo hoo.  My friend is flying in on Weds, and pay day and then I can relax and enjoy the weekend until class on Sat:(  Blue Ribbon, I'll be there soon:)

At last this long week has finally come to an end and the weekend has begun...woo hoo!  Looks like it is going to be a beautiful, perfect timing to Chinese New Yer's...go DOGS!  I am looking forward to the B-E-A beautiful weather and eating great yummy food for the new years.  Lucky me I get to celebrate both, lol.
  So this week was really great and very chilly.  Started off with me starting my new job.  It is great..5 mnth olds, so easy to take care of and oh so cute!  So that is good keeps me in bed by 2am and up by 6am and I still can keep my other jobs as well.  My other jobs went soomthly and quickly and of course getting to see BROKEBACK MOUNTAIN...GO JAKE!!GO HEATH!!!WOO HOO!   Although my internet and cable are fucked up at the moment everything else is awesome.  By the time I take off next week everything will be in order, just in time for me to come back or who knows maybe even before then!  Well enough for now..peath!

Sigh...I saw Brokeback Mountain today and I really liked it.  Besides the fact it has my Jake in it, it was a great movie.  If you are straight or gay you would love it.  It has been a long day but the movie made everything else worth it:)

Yay!  Got a new job yesterday, it is awesome.  Looking forward on earning some extra dough and of course seeing you, my dear.  Constant flirting is the fun part of the game but the not-so-fun part if trying to figure out "will you still love me tomorrow?"   But then again why think so much, when you can be enjoying the moment and for everything that is it worth.  It is great figuring out someone and their ways.  Feels good to be loved, that is never the question:)  Happy,happy, joy,joy!

Rain, Rain, go away, come again another day.  I thought hurricane season was already over, but I guess I was wrong.  Screw this Global Warming bullshit.  However, even though the weather is crap outside things are going great.  This weekend is when all the Halloween parties are happening and I was originally supposed tobe working but my employer just e-mailed me and gave me the nite off and said "go do something fun' lol.  Oh yeah and more great news then I got another job offer to Fill my mornings during the week when I have no classes:)  So thank goodness for rainy days...However, the downer is this kind of weather somehow always attracts stalkers...ewe, but at least I got two new Winter roomies...lol;)

Addicted to SIMS 2 I tell you and slowly all my friend are following in my foot steps as well.  This weekend it was so yucky outside..yucky and gloomy.  Today wasn't so bad but I stayed indoors anyhow, Winter hibernation has started early for me.  I can't tell you how great it finally feels to be single I find myself enjoying a lot more time with my friends and with myself.  It is doing great for my school work and work-wise as well.  Was supposed to go to Canada again with some friends but as usual the person who was supposed to drive canceled on us last min, but we're planning to do it next month, we just need someone to drive for us.  Anyone feel like driving for us?  At least I'm finally keeping up with writing in this LJ:)

I think Autumn is def. over or at least coming to an end fast.  I am back in NYC now and have been for about five days.  Winter seems to be following me everywhere I go.  Couldn't write any more in Toronto because we had a keyboard malfunction...lol.  Had a great time in Canada and had a safe flite back.  NYC is cold and getting depressing again.  My friend says she'll move in with me for the Winter and we can play SIMS2 all day, go to class, work, eat, smoke, and whatever.  That would be fun and I am looking forward to it.  We'll be traveling together too...lol.  So I finally relieved my slave of his duties as of today, and I hope he stays out of my life.  Don't even try to give him advice, you know who you are, because he did it to himself.  Anyways, I will try to keep up with writing, nothing much to write bout except that I am freezing my butt off.

BBBBRRRRR....it's cold.  Just thought I would start out with that considering that I am freezing my butt off here in Canada and it has been raining nonstop...ARGH!  Having a great time just spendingtime with my friend and seeing Toronto, beautiful city where everyone can be accepted.  That is awesome.  East Coast weather sucks I tell you.  Either too hot or too cold.  Seems like Spring and Fall just pass us by here, blah.  Be back in NYC on Sun.  Besides the crappy weather it is beautiful here and I love it!

wow, I really suck at keeping up with this.  See, hubby, I am still using the account...thanx for the code!
  Currently I am in Toronto and it is cold and raining.  It is much warmer than it usually is during this time of year, thanx to global warming.
  Oh I am now addicted to SIMS 2 thanx to my brother's girlfriend that bought it for my b-day!   Can you believe it 25? Now I am officially a quarter of a century old and I still look like I'm 15...lol.
  But I'll be here in Toronto till Sunday.  
  Just wanted to let everyone know that I am alive and well.  Although freezing my toes off I am still alive and kicking. 
  Summer was great.  Spent till the last week of July in NYC, working and spending time with friends.  Spent the last week of July in L.A. with the folks then went home, my bro came back too, so that was fun.  Lots of family time.
  NYC has been great...even though I am sick of this city by now.  Going on 6 yrs, I have never stayed this long in a city before...Cali is my next stop, after college, anyone else wanna come?
  I am taking my last two classes and also working.  I think that about updates everyone...more to come I promise this time.

Summer has finally officially started, as of June 1st soo has hurricane season.  It is boiling hot in the day time and gets pretty muggy, but I am not complaining as long as I don't get caught in another horrible storm like we had last nite.  The semester officially ended and I had a friend visiting me so I didn't get to update at all.  My PC officially has died on me so I am using my trusting Mac.  Haven't done much this week at all, been enjoying the Sun and catching up on my sleep.  Oh yeah sumer school has started too and I have been going to class and doing all the work that needs to be done.  Well, I thought I would update alittle anyways, no one comments any more so I doubt anyone is even reading this.

Hello again fellow readers...so I am back in school with about 13 days left till the end of the semester...then, it is finals time:(  I will be in summer school too for the first summer session..how fun is that going to be, not!  I am so tired so sorry if I am writing like a complete moron.  I haven't had any sleep since school started up again.  
  The last weekend of Spring Break was actually nice.  We went up to New Paltz and I fell in love with that village and it is so pretty, if you haven't go visit there at least once.  You can go see the house in the mountains where Stephen King wrote "The Shining".  It was good to get out of the city as well and spend some time running free about the country:)  Such a historical Village as well.  I have been so tired that I haven't been able to update so here I am doing just that.
  Today was a great day.  At schoolwe got to have our Asian Heritage Month event and we pulled it off, it was amazing and everyone came to support and the performances were awesome.  Wish you all could have been there.  It was a program with historical and cultural presentations.  I am so happy that all my friends pulled through and came out and brought there friends too:)  I am exhausted now so I am going to crash...I'll try to be on soon to keep everyone in the loop.

Happy birthday to you, happy birthday to you, happy birthday dear....u know who you are, hapy birthday to you.  Not like he reads this anyways but it is the thought that counts.
  Spring break is winding down and it is back to school again and no more time left for relaxing.  Way to many exams to take when shool starts again but on the brite side there will only be about two weeks left and then it is the end of the semester.  
   Oh yeah and for all you fellow dorks out there...i upgraded my mac today to TIGER!! WOO HOO!  Gotta love 'em geeks, dorks, nerds, whatever the hell you want to call them.  Personally I liketo refer to them as....freaking awesome people:)

Well, we missed the earlier showing at 19:50 last nite but we did get to catch the 22:10 showing and let me tell I was happy that we did.  GO RED SOX! GO JIMMY! GO DREW!  Fever pitch was a cute movie, although I know I could have easily waited and bought it on dvd I thought I would go and support Jimmy Fallon and Drew, it turned out to be a cute movie and much better than Jimmy's TAXI.  So if you are looking for a cute movie and if you are a Red Sox fan I would def. recommend this movie for you...oh and of course if you support jimmy and drew go and see it:)

Woo Hoo!  Spring Break is here and has been here since the week began.  Finally time to breath and trying to write something here in my LJ. Thanx to MAVRAX I have this journal so let me make giving me the code worth his while:)  Hey, how about a divorce?  Did that get your attention yet?
  I haven't been able to write much in here because you know life gets busy and then I forget to update journals or anything.  But I have been able to keep in contact with my friends and a lot of them have been complaining that I don't write in my LJ so they don't know what the hell is going on in my life...lol.  Well, let me see the last time I really wrote in this was way back in Aug when I was still in Shanghai.  Since then I have been back in NYC and have been really busy...btw school, student gov't, NYPIRG, work, and of course lovefatmusic.  I was reading some of my earlier entries and I remember thinking at one point if I could ever commit to just one person...well, the answer turned out to be "yes" been with the same one person for officially over 9 months and unofficially over a year now.  We have had our ups and downs, then again what relationship doesn't?  But overall it has been great.
My Student Gov't term is over on June 30th and I can not tell you how glad I will be when it is.  We had great times and got stuff done but really it took a lot out of me.  I don't know that if I ever will do it again.  I will return to NYPIRG and start doing more work with them since for the past yr I have backed off a lot because SGA took up most of my time.
  I think that about brings everyone up to date.  Still with lovefatmusic, SGA, NYPIRG and school.  I will try to update my LJ more often now since I have a laptop now it'll be easier to do.  Peath and stay tuned readers, more to come soon.
OH YEAH, I GETTO GO SEE MY JIMMY FALLON TONITE...GO RED SOX!GO JIMMY! GO DREW!

  well, i am going to get ready to start my long ass day and hopefully i will be able to write some before i end the day, but we will see.
